## Banned Phrases

These phrases are permanently banned from all editorial copy. No exceptions.

### AI Slop (delete on sight)
- "genuine differentiator"
- "occupies a curious/unique position"
- "noteworthy"
- "notable" (as a standalone adjective)
- "leveraging"
- "comprehensive" (when describing a programme)
- "robust"
- "holistic"
- "innovative"
- "cutting-edge"
- "state-of-the-art"
- "world-class" (unless quoting someone)
- "at the forefront"
- "a testament to"
- "it's worth noting that"
- "it bears mentioning"
- "in terms of"
- "when it comes to"
- "the fact that"
- "needless to say"
- "it goes without saying"
- "a wide range of"
- "a diverse range of"
- "a plethora of"
- "myriad"
- "multifaceted"
- "paradigm"
- "synergy"
- "ecosystem" (unless literally ecology)
- "landscape" (when meaning "market" or "sector")
- "navigate" (when meaning "deal with")
- "cater to"
- "boasts" (as in "the school boasts...")
- "prides itself"
- "is committed to"
- "strives to"
- "is dedicated to"
- "fosters"
- "nurtures"
- "cultivates"
- "empowers"
- "delve into"
- "explore" (when meaning "look at")

### Hedging & Corporate Speak
- "that's a feature, not a limitation"
- "this is not necessarily catastrophic"
- "the trade-off is" (bloodless framing - show the trade-off instead)
- "occupies a space between"
- "sits at the intersection of"
- "in the broader context"
- "it remains to be seen"

### Overused Cliches
- "punches above its weight" (use once per 20 profiles maximum)
- "bang for your buck"
- "hidden gem"
- "best-kept secret"
- "the gold standard"
- "a cut above"
- "raises the bar"

